Boxplot

Covariation is the tendency for the values of two or more variables to vary together in a related way.

Visualize the distribution of a categorical variable and a continuous variable using a boxplot.

data1=data[data$total!=2626.3,]
boxplot(total~payment_type, data = data1, ylab="Total expenses", xlab="Payment_type",main="Total vs Payment_type")

boxplot(distance~payment_type, data = data)
